bdglue2.publisher.kafka

Class KafkaPublisherPropertyValues

  • java.lang.Object
    • bdglue2.publisher.kafka.KafkaPublisherPropertyValues

  • public final class KafkaPublisherPropertyValues
extends Object
    This class contains configuration constants used by the Big Data Glue Kafka Publisher, including property names and where appropriate the default values to use in the event that a property is not defined.

      • KAFKA_BATCH_SIZE

        public static final String KAFKA_BATCH_SIZE

        Constant Field Values

      • KAFKA_FLUSH_FREQ

        public static final String KAFKA_FLUSH_FREQ
        The frequency to flush data if the batch size specified hasn't been reached. This prevents data from getting stale if there is a lull in volume.

      • KAFKA_REQUIRED_ACKS

        public static final String KAFKA_REQUIRED_ACKS
        Tell the producer to require an acknowledgement from the Broker that a message was received. Default is to require acknowledgement. Overriding this results in "fire and forget" which could result in data loss.
